<?xml version="1.0"?>
<html>
  <problem>
    <title>CheckPoint: Describing Simple Harmonic Motion</title>
    <parameter default="2" description="Maximum Number of Tries" type="int_pos" name="maxtries" loncapaid="11"/>
    <p>
</p><br/> 
Which of the following equations describes simple harmonic motion? <b>Check all that apply.</b>
Note that x, v, a and t stand for, respectively, position, velocity, acceleration and time. Symbol c is a positive constant.<br/>

    <part loncapaid="20">
      <optionresponse texlayout="horizontal" max="10" randomize="no" loncapaid="15">
        <ul>
          <li>
            
              <p>
                \(x=-ac\)
    </p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil1" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>
                \(dv/dt = -cx\)
    </p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil2" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>
                \(a=c(-dx/dt)\)
    </p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil3" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>
                \(dx/dt = -dv/dt\)
    </p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil4" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>
                \(c(d^2x/dt^2)=-x\)
    </p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil5" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
</optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
            
              <p>
                \(c(dv/dt)=(1/x)\)
    </p>
            
            <optioninput name="Foil6" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </optionresponse>
    </part>
  </problem>
</html>
